@startuml 32_end_to_end_component_interaction
!theme plain
title DRE 3D Framework -- End-to-End Component Interaction\nAll Use Cases: Rule Authoring | Detection | Diagnosis | Remediation

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #546E7A
  LifeLineBorderColor #B0BEC5
  ParticipantBorderColor #90A4AE
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BoxBorderColor #CFD8DC
}

box "User Layer" #FFF3E0
  actor "Data Engineer" as User
end box

box "Frontend (Databricks Apps)" #E3F2FD
  participant "Chatbot UI" as UI
end box

box "Orchestration (LangGraph)" #E8F5E9
  participant "LangGraph\nOrchestrator" as LG
  participant "Interactive\nAgents" as Agents
end box

box "AI & RAG" #FFF8E1
  participant "Mosaic AI\nLLM" as LLM
  participant "AI Search\nVector Index" as VS
end box

box "Validation Pipeline" #FFCDD2
  participant "Security\nGuard" as SecGuard
  participant "Governance\nLayer" as GovLayer
  participant "SQL\nOptimizer" as SQLOpt
  participant "Duplicate\nDetector" as DupDetect
  participant "SQL\nValidator" as SQLVal
end box

box "Unity Catalog" #E3F2FD
  database "anomaly_check_config" as RuleDB
  database "pipeline_registry" as PipelineReg
  database "incident_context" as IncidentCtx
  database "ANOMALIES" as AnomDB
  database "evidence_log" as EvidenceDB
end box

box "D1/D2/D3 Workflows" #F8BBD0
  participant "D1 Detection\nJob" as D1
  participant "D2 Diagnosis\nWorkflow" as D2
  participant "D3 Deflection\nWorkflow" as D3
end box

box "External Systems" #FFF9C4
  participant "Jira/GitHub\nConfluence" as External
  participant "Job Logs\nDelta History" as Telemetry
end box

==USE CASE 1: Rule Authoring (Interactive)==

User -> UI : "Create null check for customer email"
activate UI

UI -> LG : User query + session
activate LG

LG -> Agents : Intent Router → Retrieval Agent
activate Agents

Agents -> LLM : Optimize query\n(extract: table, column, check_type)
LLM --> Agents : Structured intent

Agents -> VS : Retrieve CAG context\n(supported_checks, security_rules)
VS --> Agents : Static catalog

Agents -> VS : Retrieve CRAG context\n(SQL patterns, examples)
VS --> Agents : Top-k chunks (confidence: HIGH)

Agents -> LLM : Generate SQL\n(grounded by CAG + CRAG)
LLM --> Agents : SQL + explanation

Agents -> SecGuard : Validate security
SecGuard -> SecGuard : Check SELECT-only,\nforbidden keywords
SecGuard --> Agents : PASSED

Agents -> GovLayer : Check governance
GovLayer -> RuleDB : Query PII catalog
RuleDB --> GovLayer : table.email = PII
GovLayer --> Agents : PII flag (requires approval)

Agents -> SQLOpt : Optimize SQL
SQLOpt -> RuleDB : Query UC metadata
RuleDB --> SQLOpt : Schema + partition info
SQLOpt -> LLM : Generate optimized SQL
LLM --> SQLOpt : Optimized + cost estimate
SQLOpt --> Agents : Optimized SQL

Agents -> DupDetect : Check duplicate
DupDetect -> VS : Vector search (similar rules)
VS --> DupDetect : Top-5 similar rules
DupDetect -> LLM : Semantic comparison
LLM --> DupDetect : No duplicate (similarity < 85%)
DupDetect --> Agents : NO_DUPLICATE

Agents -> SQLVal : Validate SQL
SQLVal -> RuleDB : DESCRIBE table
RuleDB --> SQLVal : Schema confirmation
SQLVal -> LLM : Logical validation
LLM --> SQLVal : Valid (quality: 9.2/10)
SQLVal --> Agents : VALID

Agents --> LG : Validated rule proposal
deactivate Agents

LG -> RuleDB : INSERT rule\n(status: PENDING_APPROVAL, is_active: false)
RuleDB --> LG : rule_id

LG -> External : Send approval request\n(DataGov approval for PII)

LG --> UI : Rule created\nAwaiting approval (SLA: 48h)
deactivate LG

UI --> User : "Rule DQ_20260702_001 created\nApproval request sent to DataGov"
deactivate UI

note right
  <b>Use Case 1 Complete</b>
  User creates rule via chatbot
  Multi-layer validation
  Approval sent for PII table
end note

==USE CASE 2: Rule Approval & Activation==

External -> RuleDB : Approval granted
RuleDB -> RuleDB : UPDATE rule\n(status: ACTIVE, is_active: true)
RuleDB -> User : Email notification

note right
  <b>Use Case 2 Complete</b>
  Rule approved and activated
  Now eligible for D1 execution
end note

==USE CASE 3: D1 Detection (Scheduled Execution)==

D1 -> RuleDB : SELECT rules\nWHERE is_active = true\nAND (job_tag = this_job OR frequency matches)
RuleDB --> D1 : Active rules for this job

D1 -> PipelineReg : Load pipeline metadata
PipelineReg --> D1 : Pipeline context

D1 -> D1 : Execute DQ checks\n(Z-score, null_rate, freshness, drift)

alt Anomaly Detected
  D1 -> AnomDB : INSERT anomaly\n(severity: HIGH, z_score: 3.2)
  D1 -> IncidentCtx : INSERT incident_context\n(signal_source: DATA_ANOMALY)
  D1 -> External : Send P1 alert (Jira + Email)
else No Anomaly
  D1 -> RuleDB : Log execution (status: PASS)
end

note right
  <b>Use Case 3 Complete</b>
  D1 executes active rules
  Anomaly written to Delta
  Triggers D2 workflow
end note

==USE CASE 4: Pipeline Failure Detection==

Telemetry -> D1 : Pipeline failure event\n(job_id, run_id, task_id, error)

D1 -> PipelineReg : Query pipeline metadata
PipelineReg --> D1 : owner, criticality, deps

D1 -> IncidentCtx : INSERT incident_context\n(signal_source: PIPELINE_FAILURE,\nerror_type: TASK_TIMEOUT)

D1 -> AnomDB : INSERT anomaly\n(severity: CRITICAL, failure_class: INFRA)

D1 -> D2 : Trigger diagnosis workflow
activate D2

note right
  <b>Use Case 4 Complete</b>
  Pipeline failure detected
  Unified incident_context
  Triggers D2 diagnosis
end note

==USE CASE 5: D2 Diagnosis (Async Workflow)==

D2 -> IncidentCtx : Read incident_context
IncidentCtx --> D2 : Full incident payload

D2 -> D2 : Signal Classifier\n(Pipeline failure vs Data anomaly)

D2 -> Telemetry : Retrieve job logs
Telemetry --> D2 : Task stderr/stdout

D2 -> Telemetry : Query DESCRIBE HISTORY
Telemetry --> D2 : Recent table operations

D2 -> PipelineReg : Deployment correlation\n(recent code changes?)
PipelineReg --> D2 : Git commit from 2h ago

D2 -> External : GitHub code search
External --> D2 : Recent PR changed schema

D2 -> External : Confluence runbook search
External --> D2 : Runbook: "Schema Migration SOP"

D2 -> External : ITSM prior incidents
External --> D2 : Similar incident resolved 30d ago

D2 -> VS : RAG: Search incident_kb
VS --> D2 : Similar root cause (schema mismatch)

D2 -> LLM : Compile evidence into playbook
LLM --> D2 : Root cause: Schema version mismatch\nPrescription: Rollback + schema migration

D2 -> EvidenceDB : INSERT evidence_bundle\n(job_log, delta_history, runbook, code_refs,\nsimilar_incidents, root_cause)

D2 -> D3 : Trigger deflection workflow\n(prescription + evidence_bundle)
deactivate D2

note right
  <b>Use Case 5 Complete</b>
  D2 gathers evidence
  Identifies root cause
  Compiles playbook
  Triggers D3
end note

==USE CASE 6: D3 Deflection (Approval + Remediation)==

activate D3

D3 -> EvidenceDB : Load evidence_bundle
EvidenceDB --> D3 : Complete diagnostic context

D3 -> D3 : State Validator\n(Is corruption still present?)

alt Corruption resolved externally
  D3 -> AnomDB : UPDATE status = RESOLVED_EXTERNALLY
  D3 -> User : Notification: "Issue auto-resolved"
else Corruption present
  D3 -> RuleDB : Query remediation_policy
  RuleDB --> D3 : auto_fix_allowed: false (schema change)\nblast_radius: 12 tables\napproval_required: true
  
  D3 -> D3 : Circuit Breaker\n(High blast radius → Approval Gate)
  
  D3 -> LLM : Format diagnostic summary
  LLM --> D3 : Human-readable summary
  
  D3 -> External : Jira approval ticket\n+ Email to PO/TL
  
  External -> D3 : Approval granted (click-to-approve)
  
  D3 -> D3 : Domain Executor\n(Execute schema migration playbook)
  
  D3 -> External : GitHub: Create PR with schema fix
  D3 -> Telemetry : Restart pipeline (with fix)
  
  D3 -> D3 : E2E verification\n(Re-run DQ checks)
  
  alt Fix successful
    D3 -> AnomDB : UPDATE status = RESOLVED
    D3 -> VS : Update incident_kb\n(successful resolution)
    D3 -> RuleDB : Update baseline (feedback loop)
    D3 -> User : "Incident resolved\nPipeline restarted successfully"
  else Fix failed
    D3 -> AnomDB : UPDATE status = REMEDIATION_FAILED
    D3 -> External : Escalate to L2 support
  end
end

deactivate D3

note right
  <b>Use Case 6 Complete</b>
  D3 validates state
  Routes via policy
  Human approval for high-risk
  Auto-fix + verification
  Feedback to baseline
end note

==USE CASE 7: Interactive Diagnosis Query==

User -> UI : "Why did customer pipeline fail yesterday?"
activate UI

UI -> LG : Diagnosis query
activate LG

LG -> Agents : Log Analysis Agent
activate Agents

Agents -> IncidentCtx : Query recent incidents\n(pipeline_id, date range)
IncidentCtx --> Agents : Matching incidents

Agents -> EvidenceDB : Load evidence_bundle
EvidenceDB --> Agents : Root cause + resolution

Agents -> VS : RAG: Similar incidents
VS --> Agents : Historical patterns

Agents -> LLM : Summarize diagnosis
LLM --> Agents : "Pipeline failed due to schema mismatch.\nRoot cause: Column 'email' renamed to 'email_address'.\nResolution: Schema migration applied.\nStatus: Resolved at 14:23 UTC."

Agents --> LG : Structured response
deactivate Agents

LG --> UI : Diagnosis summary
deactivate LG

UI --> User : "Pipeline failed due to schema mismatch...\n[View Evidence] [View Timeline]"
deactivate UI

note right
  <b>Use Case 7 Complete</b>
  User queries past incidents
  Agent retrieves evidence
  LLM summarizes
  Interactive response
end note

legend right
  <b>End-to-End Component Interactions Summary</b>
  
  <b>Use Case 1: Rule Authoring (Interactive)</b>
    User → UI → LangGraph → Agents
    → LLM + AI Search (CAG + CRAG)
    → Security + Governance + Validation
    → Delta (PENDING_APPROVAL)
    → External (Approval Request)
  
  <b>Use Case 2: Rule Approval</b>
    External → Delta (ACTIVE)
    → User (Notification)
  
  <b>Use Case 3: D1 Detection (Scheduled)</b>
    D1 → Delta (Read rules)
    → Execute checks
    → Delta (Write anomalies)
    → Trigger D2
  
  <b>Use Case 4: Pipeline Failure</b>
    Telemetry → D1 (Failure event)
    → Delta (incident_context)
    → Trigger D2
  
  <b>Use Case 5: D2 Diagnosis (Async)</b>
    D2 → Delta (Read incident)
    → Telemetry (Logs/History)
    → External (GitHub/Confluence/ITSM)
    → AI Search (incident_kb)
    → LLM (Playbook)
    → Delta (evidence_log)
    → Trigger D3
  
  <b>Use Case 6: D3 Deflection (Approval + Fix)</b>
    D3 → Delta (Policy/Evidence)
    → Circuit Breaker (Risk check)
    → External (Approval)
    → Execute fix
    → Verification
    → Delta (Update status + baseline)
  
  <b>Use Case 7: Interactive Diagnosis</b>
    User → UI → LangGraph → Agents
    → Delta (incident_context + evidence_log)
    → AI Search (incident_kb)
    → LLM (Summarize)
    → UI (Response)
  
  <b>Key A2A Communication Patterns:</b>
  - <b>Interactive (UC1, UC7):</b> LangGraph state
  - <b>Async (UC3-6):</b> Delta + Workflow triggers
  - <b>External:</b> REST/MCP adapters
  
  <b>Technologies Used:</b>
  - <b>Databricks Apps:</b> UI hosting
  - <b>LangGraph:</b> Agent orchestration
  - <b>Mosaic AI:</b> LLM inference
  - <b>AI Search:</b> RAG retrieval
  - <b>Unity Catalog:</b> Data layer
  - <b>Workflows:</b> D1/D2/D3 execution
  - <b>External APIs:</b> Jira/GitHub/Confluence/ITSM
endlegend

@enduml
